Next, the larvae transform into pupae, appearing suspended just below the water's surface.
Pupal mosquitoes undergo a crucial metamorphosis before emerging from their casing.
Adult mosquitoes finally emerge, equipped with wings to fly and search for bloodmeals.
The adult female mosquito requires blood to complete her reproductive cycle successfully.
Understanding these distinct stages helps control mosquito populations and prevent disease.
