The adhesive properties of spider silk are unmatched, allowing it to bind delicate structures.
Engineers are investigating spider silk's tensile strength for lightweight, durable materials.
From tiny spiders comes a complex bio-polymer with unique structural advantages.
This natural glue exhibits remarkable self-healing capabilities, promising innovative applications.
