Comparing the flower color and size is crucial when identifying wildflowers.
Field guides offer detailed illustrations necessary for plant species identification.
Knowing the blooming season helps narrow down potential wildflower candidates quickly.
Bees transfer pollen from one flower to another, ensuring plant reproduction.
