Leaves perform photosynthesis, capturing sunlight to create essential plant energy.
A vibrant flower displays its petals to attract various pollinating insects.
The stem provides structural support, holding the delicate leaves up high.
Trees grow sturdy trunks that transport water and nutrients throughout the plant.
Seed pods contain seeds, ensuring the next generation of the plant species.
The xylem and phloem are tissues moving water and sugars inside.
Blossoms open in spring, signaling the start of the plant's reproductive cycle.
