Checking for pests early catches infestations, saving your precious garden efforts.
Mulching around plants retains moisture and suppresses weeds naturally and effectively.
Composting kitchen scraps creates rich soil amendments vital for garden success.
Allowing proper airflow reduces fungal diseases, keeping your leaves healthy and clean.
The main taproot anchors the plant deeply into the soil structure.
Adventitious roots develop from stems, providing extra stability to the plant.
Fibrous root systems consist of many thin, interwoven roots near the surface.
