Many temperate flowers require seasonal cold periods to bloom properly.
Tropical species exhibit year-round growth, lacking distinct dormant cycles.
The variety of life in tropical flora exceeds temperate regions greatly.
Coastal temperate zones often feature specialized salt-tolerant plant life.
