Anther produces pollen grains, which contain the male genetic material for reproduction.
The ovary contains ovules, which develop into seeds after successful fertilization occurs.
Sepals protect the developing flower bud before it opens to the light.
Stamens are the male reproductive organs, composed of the anther and filament.
Pollen germinates on the stigma, forming a pollen tube that reaches the ovule.
The receptacle is the swollen base of the flower where all parts are attached.
