Speaking up for justice requires bravery, but blindly making accusations is merely impulsive and irresponsible.
Wisdom guides bravery, ensuring actions are impactful and measured. Recklessness simply reacts to immediate, overwhelming emotion.
The difference lies in intent: bravery aims to protect or improve, while recklessness often disregards safety entirely.
One shows resolve when facing adversity with thought. The other charges forward without a plan, merely seeking adrenaline.
