We need to negotiate the contract terms carefully, focusing especially on cancellation penalties and payment schedules to protect our budget.
Before signing the DJ agreement, request a detailed equipment list and hourly rate breakdown. Ensure the contract specifies backup plans for any technical issues.
The floral vendor quoted a high price; we must negotiate a bulk discount or negotiate a more limited, yet elegant, floral arrangement package.
Reviewing the photography contract is crucial. Make sure the agreement clearly defines the number of edited photos and the usage rights for the images.
For the catering contract, insist on a tasting session and negotiate the inclusion of specialized dietary options, like gluten-free and vegan choices.
We should negotiate a fixed rate for the entertainment vendor, rather than an hourly charge, to prevent unexpected overages during the event.
