Be mindful of parking restrictions and designated zones. Look for meters or designated lots to avoid expensive fines and towing.
When driving, observe the local driving habits of other vehicles. Adjust your speed and manner to fit the rhythm of the unfamiliar traffic flow.
Utilize public transport options when possible, especially downtown. Driving and parking can be overwhelming and time-consuming in busy centers.
It's wise to take a practice drive in a quiet neighborhood first. This will help you build confidence before tackling the main, busier thoroughfares.
Always carry physical maps as a backup to digital navigation. Technology can fail, and physical knowledge provides essential peace of mind.
