Before starting, remember to adjust the incline and speed to match your fitness level for an effective workout.
I set the treadmill to a moderate speed and walked for thirty minutes, focusing on maintaining a brisk pace.
The digital display showed my distance and calories burned, helping me track my progress on this cardio session.
To engage different muscle groups, I started with a slow walk and gradually increased the speed over time.
She preferred to jog at a consistent pace, adjusting the resistance to challenge her endurance and stamina.
