The dentist recommended using desensitizing toothpaste, advising me to brush gently. This helps block the exposed dentin tubules and soothe sensitivity.
I learned about specialized mouthwash designed for sensitive gums and teeth. Rinsing with this wash after meals helps reduce discomfort from cold drinks.
The hygienist applied a fluoride varnish directly to my teeth. This professional treatment strengthens enamel and provides immediate, temporary relief from sensitivity.
The dentist suggested modifying my diet to limit highly acidic foods. Reducing these triggers can significantly decrease the frequency of sharp, painful sensations.
We discussed using a soft-bristled toothbrush and proper brushing technique. Aggressive brushing can wear down enamel, worsening underlying tooth sensitivity issues.
For nighttime relief, the dentist prescribed a specialized toothpaste. Applying it before bed allows the active ingredients to work overnight, promoting comfort.
He demonstrated how to properly floss and brush to avoid gum irritation. Healthy gums support strong teeth, minimizing the risk of exposed, sensitive root surfaces.
The dental assistant showed me patches I can apply to sensitive areas. These temporary coverings help protect exposed nerves and provide immediate comfort.
The dental hygienist started by examining my plaque buildup. She used a specialized scaler to gently remove the sticky film from between my teeth.
Next, she grabbed the professional toothbrush. She demonstrated the proper technique for cleaning every surface, especially near the gumline.
The water flosser was incredibly effective. It blasted out stubborn debris and loosened particles that normal brushing often misses.
I watched her use a small, curved pick. This tool carefully dislodges tartar deposits that have hardened beyond simple brushing reach.
She showed me the specialized interdental brushes. These tiny brushes are perfect for cleaning the spaces between teeth that floss cannot reach.
The hygienist polished my teeth with a gritty paste. This step gives my enamel a noticeable shine and a very clean, smooth feeling.
Remember to use regular dental floss daily at home. It is crucial for removing food particles and preventing gum inflammation between brushing sessions.
She recommended a specific electric toothbrush model. It features pressure sensors to ensure I am not damaging my gums while cleaning thoroughly.
