Before the interview, prepare a list of prompts covering key life milestones. This structured approach ensures no significant period of the family's life is overlooked.
Always maintain a neutral and empathetic listening posture. Let the speaker guide the pace, creating a comfortable environment for sharing vulnerable memories.
