He always put off going to the gym, thinking he had plenty of time later. If he starts exercising consistently now, he will feel much healthier and have more energy for his hobbies. Remember that small, consistent actions accumulate into massive, positive changes over time.
My friend missed the opportunity to learn Spanish when he was in college. If he had taken that elective course, he would be fluent now, perhaps living in Madrid. He needs to remember that preparation is vital, so he plans to take intensive lessons starting next semester.
If I were wealthy, I would volunteer my time to environmental causes globally. I wouldn't just talk about change; I would fund massive reforestation projects and clean up polluted oceans. True wealth, I believe, is measured by the positive impact you make on the world.
