The scientist presented her findings at the conference yesterday. She reported that the data strongly supported the theory of climate change acceleration. She also explained that the current models underestimated the rate of polar ice melt. Several researchers nodded in agreement, acknowledging the significance of her evidence and the urgent need for global action.
