The architect stared at the blueprint, regretting the initial design choice. He should have consulted the structural engineer earlier in the process. Had he been more cautious, he could have identified the weak points before construction began. If he had incorporated the suggestions from the second team, the whole building would have been more stable and aesthetically pleasing.
