Elara looked back at the photograph of her college years, remembering the friends she drifted apart from. She should have invested more time in those relationships instead of focusing solely on her studies. If she could have maintained those bonds, her social life would have been richer and more varied. She wishes she would have been more present for them during those formative years, knowing how quickly life changes.
The chef tasted the sauce and immediately knew something was missing. He should have added a pinch of smoked paprika to enhance the depth of flavor. If he could have tasted it earlier, he wouldn't have wasted so much expensive ingredient. He believes that if he had simply adjusted the seasoning slightly, the entire dish would have achieved a gourmet balance that impressed every diner.
