When the presentation went wrong, David felt a wave of deep regret. He should have practiced his opening remarks more thoroughly before the big meeting. If he could have rehearsed in front of a larger audience, his nervousness would have been significantly reduced. He believes that if he had prepared more meticulously, he would have delivered the speech with the confidence and polish expected by the board members.
