Before the blizzard hit, the mountaineers realized they lacked proper gear. They should have packed warmer layers and emergency rations. If they could have secured reliable shelter sooner, the dangerous night would have passed safely. Since they were exposed, the climb was much harder than anticipated. They would have survived if they hadn't underestimated the severity of the weather.
