The atypical presentation warrants ruling out parasitic infection. Stool analysis for ova and parasites is essential for accurate diagnosis.
Given the history of recent travel, we must investigate zoonotic pathogens. Serological testing for Lyme disease or leptospirosis is recommended.
These findings point toward a toxigenic etiology. We need to identify the specific toxin source to guide effective supportive treatment.
