Advanced naval equipment includes remote underwater vehicles (ROVs) designed for deep-sea reconnaissance and mine clearance operations. These unmanned assets provide crucial intelligence without risking human life near volatile enemy positions. Their deployment significantly enhances the survivability and scope of the overall naval mission.
The naval doctrine emphasizes combined arms operations, integrating air support, surface combatants, and underwater assets. Coordination between fighter jets, guided missiles, and torpedoes must be flawless. This holistic approach ensures comprehensive coverage and maximizes the lethality against diverse enemy formations.
