To counter potential anti-tank ambushes, the armored column maintained a staggered formation, ensuring no single vehicle was isolated or vulnerable to concentrated fire. This defensive doctrine emphasized mutual support and rapid response capability, allowing for immediate counter-fire. Commanders stressed the importance of maintaining situational awareness across all sectors of the deployment zone.
