To hook the reader, consider starting your lede with a surprising statistic or a direct, impactful quote from a source.
Avoid weak lead phrases like 'It is reported that...' or 'Sources say...' to maintain journalistic authority and directness.
Practice condensing complex narratives into a single, powerful opening paragraph that draws the reader into the story's heart.
A compelling lede must not only inform but also create a sense of urgency, making the reader want to know more immediately.
The editor mandated that reporters strictly adhere to the AP style guide when drafting all field reports and articles.
